   <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology:
      "Chrysermus, a Corinthian, whom we find mentioned as the author of the following works :--1. A history of India, extending to at least 80 books. 2.
      A history of Persia. 3. A history of the Peloponnesus. 4. A treatise on rivers. (Plut. De Fluv. 1, 18, 20, Parall. Min. 10; Stob. Floril.
      39.31, 100.11; Phot. Bibl. 167.) The period at which he flourished is not known......" </mads:note>
